{
  "stem": "13469.8",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You were allowed to bring two people or in extraordinary circumstances three, but that was it, one wife and two children.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I was all right on the one wife, but on the two children, we actually had three children.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we had a big debate with the children about who did not have to go, because none of them actually wanted to go at first, I think.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So Simon was-- he drew the short straw and decided he didn't want to go anyway, so he didn't want to go.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "What was much more important was we also had a car parking sticker for Buckingham Palace.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they all wanted the car parking sticker to have on their cars, because they were all at university and they all had cars.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they all felt that the carpark sticker with Buckingham Palace on it would-- kind of thing-- be influential with the traffic wardens kind of thing in Solihull, so that was the bit they really wanted.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They weren't interested in going to Buckingham Palace.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Anyway, we did go to Buckingham Palace with Nick and Judith.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we arranged to meet Simon outside afterwards, but we found out later on Simon could have been our chauffeur and then he would've got in, not into the actual ceremony, but into Buckingham Palace.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "When we got into Buckingham Palace, we were-- I won't use the word now, because Corinne goes mad.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We were divided up into those people, the recipients of awards go one way and the family goes the other way.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Corinne and Nick and Judith went the other way.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they had a very nice tour of Buckingham Palace.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
